The paper discusses the problem of catastrophic forgetting in neural networks and proposes a learning to optimize algorithm for mitigating it. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments involving computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which further supports these sub-categories as likely candidates.
